name: Monster in the Jar - Specimen #002
description: Specimen #002 (Kuwlee) - Known as "Mountain Troll" in the Nepalis cultural tale, therefore they live at 2.500 - 4.000 m above sea surface. They can not survive in temperature below 10 degree Celcius. They consume small rats and fishes, so classified as carnivore. Long finger help them to climb on high trees and rock cliffs.
